text: Andriana Asprogeraka (born 17 August 1997) is a Greek taekwondo practitioner. She won a bronze medal in bantamweight at the 2015 World Taekwondo Championships, after being defeated by Lim Geum-byeol in the semifinal. She also competed at the 2017 and 2019 World Taekwondo Championships. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Greek female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists
